docs.abstract: The Senate Democratic leader wants to seek testimony from Mick Mulvaney, John Bolton and other White House officials, and subpoena documents the White House has withheld.
docs.snippet: The Senate Democratic leader wants to seek testimony from Mick Mulvaney, John Bolton and other White House officials, and subpoena documents the White House has withheld.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As the House prepared to make President Trump only the third president in American history to be impeached, the Senate’s top Democrat on Sunday laid out a detailed proposal for a Senate trial “in which all of the facts can be considered fully and fairly” — including subpoenas for documents the White House has withheld and witnesses it has prevented from testifying.

headline.main: Schumer, Pushing McConnell to Negotiate, Lays Out Plan for Impeachment Trial
headline.print_headline: Schumer Frames Full Senate Trial On Impeachment

docs.abstract: The child tax credit, begun in 1997 as a tax cut, has become an anti-poverty program. But more than a third of children don’t receive it because their parents earn too little.
docs.snippet: The child tax credit, begun in 1997 as a tax cut, has become an anti-poverty program. But more than a third of children don’t receive it because their parents earn too little.
docs.lead_paragraph: MONROE, La. — With two children and a third on the way, Ciera Dismuke worked five jobs last year while earning just under $15,000. Although the Trump administration often boasts that it doubled the federal child tax credit to $2,000 per child, Ms. Dismuke, like millions of Americans, earned too little to fully qualify. Instead, she got $934 a child, an increase of just $75.

headline.main: The Tax Break for Children, Except the Ones Who Need It Most
headline.print_headline: Tax Credit for Children Leaves Neediest Behind

docs.abstract: The regulations will allow a wider group of investors to profit from the 2017 tax provision that was pitched as a boon to low-income areas.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration finished regulations this week that will make it easier for wealthy Americans to invest in and benefit from opportunity zones, a tax incentive created in 2017 that was intended to funnel investment into low-income communities.

headline.main: Treasury Completes Rules for Opportunity Zone Tax Breaks

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Monica Crowley, the Treasury Department’s assistant secretary for public affairs, committed “localized instances of plagiarism” in her 2000 Ph.D. dissertation, Columbia University found in an investigation that ultimately concluded she did not commit research misconduct.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The United States accused President Nicolás Maduro of Venezuela on Friday of trying to rig a coming election for control of his country’s parliament, either by detaining opposition leaders or bribing lawmakers with up to $500,000 for each vote.

headline.main: U.S. Accuses Venezuela’s President of Rigging Coming Vote
